eYVz\" style=\"position: relative;flex-direction: column;align-items: center;padding: 0;width: auto;height: auto;border: none;text-decoration: none;display: block;margin: 0;margin-top: 0;margin-bottom: 0;\"><img class=\"wide-image\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/0a03cb44-05e1-44dd-9510-6f35c1e4b35f_6000x4000.heic&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:971,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:3338680,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/heic&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://www.bemorerelatable.com&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"366.7925824175824\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!3lo5!,w_1100,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F0a03cb44-05e1-44dd-9510-6f35c1e4b35f_6000x4000.heic\" style=\"border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;height: auto;margin-bottom: 0;width: auto !important;max-width: 100% !important;margin: 0 auto;\"></a></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td></tr></tbody></table></figure></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><strong><span>Hey it&#8217;s Zvi! You&#8217;ve been a subscriber of my newsletter, </span><a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx0kDvOnTAQRleDu6CL3xQu0txtID_G4FywkT0OIquP-NOk-etPM-foeIuwlnqbnmPKqW0QfrTumq_pxFQyCYaHSQtNwExKKTopqSWBw6Z9WSFDtQhhsfjfKuRMNgMhMBdiFHFik5yVkIFpzxS3NjLJI0mGvqh8cSonwTiXIxspVVxaLt0sZs2AjSyuv_5cnQ_8dax0fMzQ-s_oy0FSW2KFLxODtQPZzYZ4toH9HOh7oO8MV9sBEero4CgVKuwWrdvhuR_om5zdLb4cR88J7wXys4V_z87u9uTt02BJwWiplVKCVHM1v0H-DPy1PugvldZdKIdN2dyl1wx4lfppaCu2K-F2l07w28K9QX0QVDA9cUp-G_o3AAD__wlQiYY\" style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underline;\">Be More Relatable</a><span>. I have three updates:</span></strong></p><ol style=\"margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;margin: 0;\">I&#8217;ve moved over from our old newsletter platform to Substack.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;margin: 0;\">The newsletter is renamed from Be More Relatable to Your Network Starts with You.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;margin: 0;\"><span>I still have not found the </span><em>perfect</em><span> breakfast burrito.</span></p></li></ol><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>There is </span><em>nothing</em><span> you have to do here. </span></p><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;\">Why Substack?</h3><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Our old newsletter platform, which I had been using from day 1, is fantastic. Substack has a few things that I felt would be helpful - including better video and podcast integration (which I want to start doing) and a good mobile app. I also want to grow our audience, and Substack has a fantastic community for that.</p><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;\">Why the name change?</h3><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>Relatable is the name of my super awesome CRM (</span><a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx0kDtyrDAQRVeDskeB_hMoeMlsg9KnAXlAoqSWKbx6F-PEieNbt8_p6y3CkstlWppjinWF8K82V32JB8acSDA8jFpoAmZUStFRSS0J7DZu0wIJikUIk8VfqZAPshrtIOjBawjzIJ0SnNGBzxRmEME7xUk0dKBy4FSOgnEue9ZTqri0XLqHeGgGrGfz8vF1Nt7xYV9of5uh9a_e553EOs0F3iYGSwOymRXxqB3739FnR58O9lygwGbRug3epaO5yed9byniNUG6g_BTP5rborf311MMRkutlBKkmLP6FdKr48Nyw953anMh7zYmc-VWEuCZy6uiLVjPiOuVG8E_N20Vyo2ggumRU_Jp6HcAAAD__9qrhJc\" style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underline;\">do you use it yet?</a><span>), and it was getting confusing. More importantly, however, I felt it didn&#8217;t convey one of my deepest beliefs. The most effective and thriving relationships rely on being deeper in touch with yourself. Knowing the kind of people and things that bring you energy. Being comfortable sharing more about yourself. Being more aware of the stories that have prevented you from being more in touch with other people. So&#8230; I do really believe that your network starts with you.</span></p><h3 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.375em;\">Why have you not found a good breakfast burrito?</h3><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Honestly, I&#8217;m setting myself up for failure.</p><ul style=\"margin-top: 0;padding: 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;margin: 0;\">I don&#8217;t eat pork, so chorizo is out.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;margin: 0;\">I limit dairy, so cheese is a &#8220;if absolutely worth it&#8221; kinda thing.</p></li><li style=\"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;mso-special-format: bullet;\"><p style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;margin-bottom: 0;box-sizing: border-box;padding-left: 4px;font-size: 16px;margin: 0;\">I live in Maryland, far away from the meccas of LA and SF.</p></li></ul><h2 class=\"header-anchor-post\" style=\"position: relative;font-family: 'SF Pro Display',-apple-system-headline,system-ui,-apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,'Segoe UI',Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif,'Apple Color Emoji','Segoe UI Emoji','Segoe UI Symbol';font-weight: bold;-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;-moz-osx-font-smoothing: antialiased;-webkit-appearance: optimizelegibility;-moz-appearance: optimizelegibility;appearance: optimizelegibility;margin: 1em 0 0.625em 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 1.16em;font-size: 1.625em;\">If you want&#8230; allow me to reintroduce myself.</h2><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Every once in a while, I find it helpful to pull back and reset expectations - for me and for you.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Networking, as most people think about it, doesn&#8217;t work. It feels awkward, transactional, and forced, turning relationships into a numbers game that most people can tell is off. At the same time, relationships are still the thing. Every meaningful opportunity in your career or business comes from a person, not an algorithm or a cold outreach sequence, but a real connection with someone who knows you and trusts you.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">That&#8217;s the tension most people are stuck in. They know relationships matter, but they don&#8217;t want to network. This publication exists to close that gap. I write about how relationships actually work in real life, not through scripts, hacks, or surface-level advice, but through the long-term reality of staying connected to people in a way that feels natural and sustainable.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Most people don&#8217;t lose relationships because they don&#8217;t care. They lose them because they don&#8217;t have a system. They rely on memory and good intentions. They tell themselves they will reach out soon, and then life gets busy and those relationships slowly fade. Most importantly, they get in their own way, because of the stories in their head. Sound familiar?</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Your relationships deserve better than that. They deserve more than a spreadsheet, more than a CRM built for sales teams, and more than a vague reminder to stay in touch. They deserve a system that reflects how relationships actually work over time.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Each week, I share clear thinking, practical tactics, and simple systems you can actually use. The goal is not to give you more to do. The goal is to help you stay connected to the right people consistently, without it feeling like work. When relationships are handled well, they compound. They open doors, create opportunities, and make your work easier and more meaningful.</p><div class=\"captioned-image-container-static\" style=\"font-size: 16px;line-height: 26px;margin: 32px auto;\"><figure style=\"width: 100%;margin: 0 auto;\"><table class=\"image-wrapper\" width=\"100%\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" data-component-name=\"Image2ToDOMStatic\" style=\"mso-padding-alt: 1em 0 1.6em;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td><td class=\"content\" align=\"left\" width=\"1456\" style=\"text-align: center;\"><a class=\"image-link\" target=\"_blank\" href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx0kDtyrDAQRVeDskeB_hMoeMlsg9KnAXlAoqSWKbx6F-PEieNbt8_p6y3CkstlWppjinWF8K82V32JB8acSDA8jFpoAmZUStFRSS0J7DZu0wIJikUIk8VfqZAPshrtIOjBawjzIJ0SnNGBzxRmEME7xUk0dKBy4FSOgnEue9ZTqri0XLqHeGgGrGfz8vF1Nt7xYV9of5uh9a_e553EOs0F3iYGSwOymRXxqB3739FnR58O9lygwGbRug3epaO5yed9byniNUG6g_BTP5rborf311MMRkutlBKkmLP6FdKr48Nyw953anMh7zYmc-VWEuCZy6uiLVjPiOuVG8E_N20Vyo2ggumRU_Jp6HcAAAD__9qrhJc\" style=\"position: relative;flex-direction: column;align-items: center;padding: 0;width: auto;height: auto;border: none;text-decoration: none;display: block;margin: 0;\"><img class=\"wide-image\" data-attrs=\"{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/5e5c6f67-7536-4d6b-aed3-f229b387c525_6000x4000.heic&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:971,&quot;width&quot;:1456,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:null,&quot;bytes&quot;:3247489,&quot;alt&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/heic&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:&quot;https://bemorerelatable.com&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null,&quot;isProcessing&quot;:false,&quot;align&quot;:null,&quot;offset&quot;:false}\" alt=\"\" title=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"366.7925824175824\" src=\"https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/$s_!Oc35!,w_1100,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F5e5c6f67-7536-4d6b-aed3-f229b387c525_6000x4000.heic\" style=\"border: none !important;vertical-align: middle;display: block;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;height: auto;margin-bottom: 0;width: auto !important;max-width: 100% !important;margin: 0 auto;\"></a></td><td style=\"text-align: center;\"></td></tr></tbody></table></figure></div><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\"><span>I&#8217;m Zvi. I&#8217;m a relationship-building strategist for professionals who hate the word networking, the author of Success is in Your Sphere, and the founder of </span><a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx0kDtyrDAQRVeDskeB_hMoeMlsg9KnAXlAoqSWKbx6F-PEieNbt8_p6y3CkstlWppjinWF8K82V32JB8acSDA8jFpoAmZUStFRSS0J7DZu0wIJikUIk8VfqZAPshrtIOjBawjzIJ0SnNGBzxRmEME7xUk0dKBy4FSOgnEue9ZTqri0XLqHeGgGrGfz8vF1Nt7xYV9of5uh9a_e553EOs0F3iYGSwOymRXxqB3739FnR58O9lygwGbRug3epaO5yed9byniNUG6g_BTP5rborf311MMRkutlBKkmLP6FdKr48Nyw953anMh7zYmc-VWEuCZy6uiLVjPiOuVG8E_N20Vyo2ggumRU_Jp6HcAAAD__9qrhJc\" style=\"color: rgb(54,55,55);text-decoration: underline;\">Relatable</a><span>. I used to believe that doing good work was enough and that if I focused on results, everything else would follow. But when I looked back at my own career, every meaningful moment traced back to a person. It was always a real relationship, not a transaction. That realization changed how I think about work.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">For the past 14 years, I&#8217;ve been focused on one question: why do some people build strong, lasting professional relationships while everyone else just collects contacts? The answer isn&#8217;t personality or charisma. It&#8217;s having a system and actually using it.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">I built Contactually, a relationship-focused CRM that was eventually acquired and is now used by hundreds of thousands of people. I wrote Success is in Your Sphere to share the framework behind authentic, long-term relationship building, and I built Relatable, a CRM designed around people instead of pipelines.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">When I&#8217;m not building software, writing about authentic connections, or helping people rethink how they approach relationships, I&#8217;m usually exploring my own personal growth, searching for the spiciest hot sauce I can find, drinking more matcha than I probably should, or convincing myself I&#8217;ll respond to that message in just a few minutes. I live just outside Washington, DC with my wife, two kids, and one very obnoxious golden retriever.</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">Zvi</p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;\">PS: If you&#8217;re here, you probably already know this. You don&#8217;t need more people. You need to stay connected to the right ones. That&#8217;s what this is about. </p><p style=\"margin: 0 0 20px 0;color: rgb(54,55,55);line-height: 26px;font-size: 16px;margin-bottom: 0;\"><span>PPS: Upgrade to the </span><a href=\"https://email.mg2.substack.com/c/eJx00D2OpDAQBeDT4GwR-J_AwSZ9DWTjArwNNrLLi5jTj-iRRjNBBxWVVO-rN1mEJeXL1DiHGMoK_k-prkw5HBhSJN5w32uhCZheKUV7JbUksNuwjQtEyBbBjxZ_bIUcyGqEA9FL36lBMuWUGOTsKGdaeN3NTM0kGNpR2XEqe8E4ly1rKV